guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"3cp8q","text":"Gives reasonable quality and yield of gDNA. Ideal for DNA in PCRs applications, Dye-terminator Sanger sequencing reactions, and cloning. Can be used for next-generation sequencing applications, however, ensure you perform additional cleaning steps and longer centrifuge times. Run on a 1% agarose gel to ensure you have good quality and clean DNA preparation (and Nanodrop), often these preps yield a substantial portion of sheared nucleotides (likely RNA, so make sure you add RNase A during extraction).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2rf36","text":"Aliquot required volume of CTAB buffer and heat in water bath at 60 ºC for 5-10 minutes immediately before use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9ku5k","text":"Cool samples to room temperature .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"lebi","text":"Add 300 µL chloroform and mix thoroughly with a vortex or vigorous shaking for 15 seconds. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3o8uf","text":"Centrifuge samples for 10 minutes at 20,000 rcf.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5jofe","text":"Add equal volume of ice-cold 2-propanol and mix by inversion.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"61ore","text":"Centrifuge for 15 min @ 20,000 rcf.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"38lnv","text":"Wash pellet with 1 mL of 70 % ethanol (mix by inversion).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"82sp5","text":"Resuspend gDNA in nuclease-free H2O or low EDTA TE buffer (10 mM Tris-Cl pH 8, 0.1 mM EDTA). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":33,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f0ue4","text":"Prepare 2% CTAB buffer. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7ec9j","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"62h96","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"aso6t","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"tables","mutability":"","data":{"cellsMeta":{"A_1":{"className":"_dt-bold"},"B_1":{"className":"_dt-bold"}},"colTitles":["",""],"colWidths":["247",100],"data":[["Reagent","[Cf]"],["hexadecyltrimethylammonium bromide","2% (w/v)"],["NaCl","1.4 M"],["EDTA (pH 8)","20 mM"],["Tris-Cl (pH 8)","100 mM"]],"guid":"FB7179D0A2F411EB9561815EE8668BDF","isJexcelDataFormat":true,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1pja2","text":"2% CTAB buffer recipe","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mergeCells":{},"printData":[["Reagent","[Cf]"],["hexadecyltrimethylammonium bromide","2% (w/v)"],["NaCl","1.4 M"],["EDTA (pH 8)","20 mM"],["Tris-Cl (pH 8)","100 mM"]],"rowHeights":[23,23,23,23,23]}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4jv0o","text":"Add 300 µL / 100 mg leaf tissue of CTAB buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"akqbj","text":"Add RNase A solution to a concentration 50-100 µg/mL.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"94rb9","text":"Mix well with a vortex. Invert samples by hand to ensure that all ground tissue is in solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cgmnq","text":"Incubate in water bath at 60 ºC for 30 - 60 minutes. Mix tubes periodically by inversion.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2e3e4","text":"Transfer upper aqueous (approx. 200 µL) phase to clean tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7demi","text":"Repeat steps 9-10 for a cleaner extract.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"d9hls","text":"Incubate for 30-60 min @ -20 °C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fn9kn","text":"Discard supernatant using pipette.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3pr9r","text":"Centrifuge samples @ 9,200 rcf for 5 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8neuo","text":"Remove as much ethanol as possible using a pipette, then allow pellet to air dry for 5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fo8na","text":"Test yield and purity of samples using a Nanodrop and running samples on a 1 % agarose gel.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
